This comparison is not appropriate if we want to verify that the model's position has changed. See below, an example of 2 objects that represent the same position but === returns false:

$ node
> x= {x:1,y:1}
{ x: 1, y: 1 }
> y={x:1, y:1}
{ x: 1, y: 1 }
> x == y
false
> x === y
false
